52.8	Wolverine	Wolverine	The wolverine, pronounced , Gulo gulo (Gulo is Latin for "glutton"), also referred to as glutton, carcajou, skunk bear, or quickhatch, is the largest land-dwelling species of the family Mustelidae (weasels). It is a stocky and muscular carnivore, more closely resembling a small bear than other mustelids. The wolverine has a reputation for ferocity and strength out of proportion to its size, with the documented ability to kill prey many times its size.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0a/Gulo_gulo_2.jpg/220px-Gulo_gulo_2.jpg
